        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 12:16PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1216 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Air Force Academy, or 9 miles north of Colorado Springs, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colorado Springs, Air Force Academy, Falcon, Cimarron Hills, Peterson
Space Force Base, Gleneagle, and Security-Widefield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
